## Notion writing conventions

- **Working Notes** on Active Package page = source of truth for per-customer state.
- **Prep briefs** go inside a `📋 Prep — YYYY-MM-DD` toggle on the Session page.
- **KDD sub-pages** (architecting sessions only) = child pages of the Session page, titled `KDDs — <Session ID> <Name>`.
- **Tasks** — every Task must have a `Customers` relation set. For internal/non-customer-specific tasks, point to the Productboard customer record at `https://www.notion.so/29997e9c7d4f80e6a011f053bdec1ab5`.

## Accounts the user has explicit context about

The full list of currently-owned accounts is queried live from Notion (`Customer.Owner LIKE '%<user-uuid>%'`). For inherited accounts with rich handover context, see the `🧠 Working Notes` toggle on the Active Package page in Notion.

Cross-customer patterns and observations are kept in [`context/tracker-memory.md`](../context/tracker-memory.md).
